LINE 2 TRADITIONALLY CALLED FINANCIAL AID PACKAGING "NEED" IS DEFINED AS THE COST OFATTENDANCE COA (TUITION, FEES, BOOKS, ROOM & BOARD,TRANSPORTATION,AND PERSONAL EXPENSES) MINUS THE EXPECTED FAMILY CONTRIBUTION EFC AS DETERMINED BY THE U S DEPARTMENT OF EDUCATION NEED ANALYSIS FORMULAE THE COORDINATION OFINSTITUTIONAL GRANT AID OCCURS SUBSEQUENT TO THE FEDERAL REGULATIONS REQUIREMENT THAT FEDERAL AND STATE GRANT AID AWARDS BE DETERMINED FIRST A DETERMINATION OF AN INSTITUTIONAL "SCHOLARSHIP" AWARD IS BASED ON ACADEMIC MERIT (CUMULATIVE GRADE POINT AVERAGE) ACHIEVED IN HIGH SCHOOL OR A PREVIOUS COLLEGE A DETERMINATION OFAN INSTITUTIONAL "GRANT" AWARD IS BASED ON "REMAINING NEED " A STUDENT MAY RECEIVE BOTH A MERIT AND NEED AWARD ONE-HALF OF EACH AWARD IS PAID IN EACH OFTWO SEMESTERS,WHICH IS CALLED AN "ACADEMIC YEAR " ANNUAL AGGREGATE BUDGET MAXIMUMS ARE ESTABLISHED FOR EACH INSTITUTIONAL AID AWARD TITLE ACTUAL AWARDS TO STUDENTS ARE MADE BY THE DIRECTOR OF FINANCIAL AID THE DIRECTOR OF INSTITUTIONAL COMPLIANCE AND THE CHIEF FINANCIAL OFFICER MONITORS THE NUMBER OF,AND AMOUNTS OF, INSTITUTIONAL AID AWARDED TO ENROLLED STUDENTS ON A MONTHLY BASIS THROUGHOUT THE ACADEMIC YEAR QUARTERLY STUDENT FILE REVIEWS ARE CONDUCTED TO ENSURE THAT ALL FEDERAL, STATE AND INSTITUTIONAL AID AWARDS DO NOT EXCEED THE STUDENT'S INITIAL "NEED " ANY AWARD DETERMINED TO EXCEED NEED IS ADJUSTED IN THE SUBSEQUENT SEMESTER AS A CORRECTIVE ACTION AT THE END OF THE ACADEMIC YEAR,A SUMMARY OFTHE AWARDS AND EXPENDITURES MADE IS REVIEWED WITH THE VICE PRESIDENT FOR FINANCE AND THE PROVOST SO THAT MERIT OR NEED AID BUDGET ADJUSTMENTS, IF ANY,ARE IN PLACE FORTHE SUBSEQUENT ACADEMIC YEAR
